title: Lightly Unmotivated.
body:
I just planned a REALLY fun workout that I’m excited about, but for some reason I’m still lacking motivation to go to the gym! I feel like I’d rather go for a walk outside. However, I think my body would really benefit from a little more intensity and it’s important to me to not let resistance completely fall by the wayside just because I’ve decided to hit pause on powerlifting.

So, what I’m going to do is get my butt to the gym and start the workout. I’ll either get into it or I won’t, and if that’s the case then I can walk out the door and literally across the street to the walking path and take my walk. And that is how we compromise!

The Navy coach’s perspective on 2018 Notre Dame, thus, carries historical significance.
